item.title: Teleporting
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

lol space:

Those are the ids on any other server I’ve coded, so they should be and I think they are Hypereon

Hyperon wasn’t the one asking about the IDs, I was.
And just because they’re the same on “Any other server I’ve coded” (your words), doesn’t mean they always will be.
Lets say for instance, you always work on servers with 474 magic book interfaces… And then this server has a 508 spell tab interface (Not saying it does). Now, chances are (key word: chances) the ids will have stayed the same, but you cannot be certain. Why? Everyone is different.
Some people release interfaces overriding the old ones, and some just make a whole new interface from scratch, and I believe lins interface editor/maker just used the next available id… Lets say someone did override the old spellbook interface ids with the new one… What if that new spellbook has 2 new spells? What would those IDs be? Exactly.

Use a for loop to replace all the ids on your spellbook and verify the ids are correct… That should have been step 1.
